If you are not familiar with the tool, it won't be easy to understand if the databse is with a danger allocation.

Resolution:
- Create a simple REXX code to adapt the report (previous example) removing unnecessary text, spaces and move the "columns" sorting the file
- To create a historical in Mainframe, it was created a generation dataset with 10 generations. The report runs weekly.
- The current report is sent via e-mail to a specific microsoft distribution list, only to keep the files available.
- Then, the Microsoft Power Automate reads the distribution list and moves the attachment to a folder in OneDrive, modifying the name adding the current date.
- Power BI gets this new report and add the new information to the dashboard.

Outcome:
The dashboard is adapted to show all the databases and current space utilization. If you want to see an specific one, you can choose in a selection the one that you desire and a line graph will show the trends of this specific base is stable or not.

This can helps the application team and the database administrators to have the database usage quickly and take decisions about business requirements.

Due legal reasons, I cannot show the real report or the power BI dashboard.

